# fh-matui


<!-- WARNING: THIS FILE WAS AUTOGENERATED! DO NOT EDIT! -->

## What is fh-matui?

**fh-matui** is a Python library that brings Google‚Äôs Material Design to
[FastHTML](https://fastht.ml/) applications. It provides a comprehensive
set of pre-built UI components that integrate seamlessly with FastHTML‚Äôs
hypermedia-driven architecture.

Built on top of [BeerCSS](https://www.beercss.com/) (a lightweight
Material Design 3 CSS framework), fh-matui enables you to create modern,
responsive web interfaces entirely in Python ‚Äî no JavaScript required.

## ‚ú® Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|----|----|
| üé® **Material Design 3** | Modern, beautiful components following Google‚Äôs latest design language |
| ‚ö° **Zero JavaScript** | Build interactive UIs entirely in Python with FastHTML |
| üì± **Responsive** | Mobile-first design with automatic breakpoint handling |
| üåô **Dark Mode** | Built-in light/dark theme support with 20+ color schemes |
| üß© **Composable** | Chainable styling APIs inspired by MonsterUI |
| üìä **Data Tables** | Full-featured tables with pagination, search, sorting, and CRUD |
| üîß **nbdev-powered** | Literate programming with documentation built from notebooks |

